that we had of him and the image that his

00:25:01.900 --> 00:25:02.900
rivals had of him.

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:06.320
Because he was a brute and a bully.

00:25:06.320 --> 00:25:08.500
&gt;&gt;Daniel: Particularly in this Tour de France
that your book is about.

00:25:08.500 --> 00:25:14.160
&gt;&gt;Richard: Yeah the books about the 86' tour
where he and the American Greg LeMond lined

00:25:14.160 --> 00:25:15.860
up in the same La Vie Claire team.

00:25:15.860 --> 00:25:21.070
The previous year in 85', Hinault had won
his fifth tour.

00:25:21.070 --> 00:25:22.860
But he'd done so with the help of LeMond.

00:25:22.860 --> 00:25:25.970
I mean he probably wouldn't have won that
tour had LeMond not helped them.

00:25:25.970 --> 00:25:30.730
He had a terrible crash Saint-Étienne and
sort of finished the race with a broken nose

00:25:30.730 --> 00:25:32.400
and bronchitis, two black eyes.

00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:33.410
It looked brilliant.

00:25:33.410 --> 00:25:36.730
[laughter]
But he struggled to the line and LeMond had

00:25:36.730 --> 00:25:38.070
helped him.

00:25:38.070 --> 00:25:41.710
And LeMond probably had his chance to win
that tourney, he held back on team orders

00:25:41.710 --> 00:25:43.130
in order to help Hinault.

00:25:43.130 --> 00:25:46.910
And Hinault allegedly promised him that he
would help him the following year which was

00:25:46.910 --> 00:25:49.780
Hinault's final tour in '86.

00:25:49.780 --> 00:25:52.470
And he made this pledge to help LeMond to
win it.

00:25:52.470 --> 00:25:55.550
And he made it to several people LeMond himself
and to journalist.

00:25:55.550 --> 00:26:00.220
But of course as the '86 tour approaches,
people are starting to question whether Hinault

00:26:00.220 --> 00:26:02.220
will honor the pledge.

00:26:02.220 --> 00:26:06.150
And he has, you know the President of France
urging him to forget about it.

00:26:06.150 --> 00:26:12.170
The whole French media and people really you
know forget about the American.

00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:14.700
You know go for the sixth tour which would've
been historic.

00:26:14.700 --> 00:26:19.100
You know in front of Merckx and Anquetil as
a six-time winner.

00:26:19.100 --> 00:26:21.460
So the temptation was huge.

00:26:21.460 --> 00:26:26.110
And really as the tour began it seemed to
be very much open.

00:26:26.110 --> 00:26:29.290
And as it began, and as it went into its first
week and then hit the tourneys, it became

00:26:29.290 --> 00:26:33.991
very very obvious to everybody, especially
LeMond that Hinault was not going to help

00:26:33.991 --> 00:26:36.490
LeMond, he was out to try to win it himself.

00:26:36.490 --> 00:26:41.440
So what followed was this fascinating kind
of internal battle between them and their

00:26:41.440 --> 00:26:42.500
own team.

00:26:42.500 --> 00:26:46.929
And the team you know ended up being split
and down the middle really, with the Swiss

00:26:46.929 --> 00:26:49.420
riders in the middle as neutrals.

00:26:49.420 --> 00:26:51.250
And it was fascinating.

00:26:51.250 --> 00:26:55.790
&gt;&gt;Daniel: Two very contrasting characters,
but you had two very contrasting experiences

00:26:55.790 --> 00:27:00.660
of Etienne, talk a little bit about them
&gt;&gt;Richard: Yeah, I mean Hinault.

00:27:00.660 --> 00:27:04.510
LeMond is very open and friendly and warm.

00:27:04.510 --> 00:27:08.970
Whereas Hinault is very cold and coarse and
short.

00:27:08.970 --> 00:27:15.470
And I went into LeMond, you know the book
is, it's funny because the book is about LeMond

00:27:15.470 --> 00:27:16.470
and Hinault.

00:27:16.470 --> 00:27:20.160
But Hinault is the person that really seems
to fascinate people.

00:27:20.160 --> 00:27:22.510
But LeMond is equally fascinating in his own
way.

00:27:22.510 --> 00:27:28.370
He was this kinda young prodigy who wasn't
streetwise in the way that Hinault was, he

00:27:28.370 --> 00:27:30.150
was just hugely, hugely talented.

00:27:30.150 --> 00:27:34.490
But he was wracked by insecurity, by doubt,
by fragility.

00:27:34.490 --> 00:27:37.560
And it was not just a physical.

00:27:37.560 --> 00:27:39.250
&gt;&gt;Ned: Wracked by diarrhea at one point.

00:27:39.250 --> 00:27:40.250
&gt;&gt;Richard: Wracked by diarrhea.

00:27:40.250 --> 00:27:43.010
It was not just physical battle between them,
it was the psychological battle.

