have been better.

00:28:00.490 --> 00:28:01.910
I mean he was brilliant.

00:28:01.910 --> 00:28:07.059
And just the stories that will come out of
him were just incredible.

00:28:07.059 --> 00:28:08.890
Such a contrast to Hinault.

00:28:08.890 --> 00:28:16.360
He's become more, because Hinault you know
did subject him to a very horrendous experience

00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:18.400
during that tour.

00:28:18.400 --> 00:28:22.920
You know I think it was pretty, it was pretty
hard and pretty harrowing.

00:28:22.920 --> 00:28:25.540
But he's kind of softened to Hinault over
the years.

00:28:25.540 --> 00:28:26.760
He's kind forgiven him in a way.

00:28:26.760 --> 00:28:29.830
Because I think he understands now why Hinault
did it.

00:28:29.830 --> 00:28:31.490
Why it was important to him.

00:28:31.490 --> 00:28:35.702
I don't think, I think for Hinault to have
been seen to be just basically riding in the

00:28:35.702 --> 00:28:39.550
service of LeMond I think it would've damaged
Hinault 's legacy.

00:28:39.550 --> 00:28:43.059
And I think Hinault kind of on some level
realized that.

00:28:43.059 --> 00:28:47.500
And so the only way for him to help LeMond
or to be beaten was to kind of go down all

00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:49.570
guns blazing in the way that he did.

00:28:49.570 --> 00:28:53.870
