The most disappointing memory, or recent memory
of Andy Shleck is interviewing him on the

00:49:16.140 --> 00:49:19.869
Champs-Elysees last year at the tour where
he finished in second.

00:49:19.869 --> 00:49:22.000
And I said, "Andy, sum it all up.

00:49:22.000 --> 00:49:24.079
Now you're here, you've reached Paris.

00:49:24.079 --> 00:49:26.170
When you look back in 10 years, what will
you think about this tour."

00:49:26.170 --> 00:49:31.210
And he said, "I'm immensely proud to finish
second in the Tour de France."

00:49:31.210 --> 00:49:34.900
[laughter]
He should've won it, last year he should've

00:49:34.900 --> 00:49:35.900
won it.

